cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the geometric representation of trees.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the optimal embedding of trees.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial embeddings of trees.
- cs.GT (Graph Theory) is relevant as trees are a type of graph and the paper discusses their embeddings.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper shows that testing whether a given binary tree has an upward embedding with a given combinatorial embedding in a given grid is NP-hard.
